    "Research in contextEvidence before this study Our research team executed a comprehensive search on PubMed, targeting literature that assesses the e cacy of Large Language Models (LLMs) in addressing queries pertaining to adolescent growth and development.",
    "We imposed no constraints regarding the date or language of the publications.",
    "The search strategy involved the integration of terms linked to LLMs (such as 'Large Language Model', 'ChatGPT', 'Google Bard') with keywords relevant to pediatrics ('Adolescent Growth', 'Adolescent Development').",
    "Our ndings revealed that while existing research predominantly evaluates the pro ciency of LLMs in standardized pediatric exams, there's a noticeable research gap concerning their application speci cally to adolescent growth and development topics.",
    "[References 1 -4] Added value of this study Our investigation distinctively focused on comparing the e cacy of three LLM-Chatbots in answering 100 typical questions related to adolescent growth and development, a notable shift from earlier studies that primarily examined standard questions from ophthalmology exams."
